    GO allows multiple return fields
    How to define a GO type to replace GroupItem
    How to use GO packages to replace C++ utilities
        GO has slices and ranges, fundamental concepts to GO that do not currently exist in incant
        GO map can probably replace group list
        GO bit vector can replace bitMAP
    Replacing double linked list in GroupItem with GO array
        IWC use index as a field offset into its parent array (ie; eliminate nextInParent and priorInParent)
    Argument handling
        When interpreting, arguments are resolved as if they are global fields. Should not be a problem w/GO actions as long as it runs in the incant runtime (which is interpreted but can invoke GO actions???)
        A global reference in a GO action will have to be resolved - how to make this happen automagically???
            a registered local field would require set up to find it. Only needed if such local fields exist. generateCode() should figure out if it has to and insert a setup(action) call to do it
    
